explored automating a data pipeline from an e-commerce website to a MongoDB database using a Python script-----
steps---
1. Install pymongo requests in your terminal

2.run Python script
 from pymongo import MongoClient
client = MongoClient("mongodb://localhost:27017/") / --mongodb local connection string
db = client["ecommerce"]
collection = db["products"]------set db and collection name

3 fetch data from API------
import requests
response = requests.get("https://lnkd.in/gvTfqzmz")
data = response.json()

4. scrapped data insert into MongoDB ---

if isinstance(data, list):
  collection.insert_many(data)
else:
  collection.insert_one(data)
print("âœ… Data inserted successfully into MongoDB!")

5. check data into mongoshell ----

use ecommerce
db.products.find().limit(3).pretty()

